-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                    Preamble
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The intent of this document is to state the conditions under which the ANNEVO
software package may be used, copied, modified, and distributed. The goal is to
allow academic institutions and non-profit organizations to freely use the
software for research purposes, while preserving the copyright holder’s rights
to control and license commercial usage.

This license is designed to ensure that academic users can benefit from ANNEVO
without restriction, but that any commercial usage requires a separate
commercial license agreement.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                  Definitions
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

For the purposes of this license:

- “Academic Use” means use by accredited academic institutions and non-profit
  research organizations for non-commercial research and education.

- “Commercial Use” means any use by a commercial entity, or use intended for
  commercial advantage or monetary compensation. This includes, but is not
  limited to, use in commercial products or services, contract research,
  fee-for-service activities, or collaborations where results are intended
  for commercial purposes.

